1
00:00:01.919 --> 00:00:02.798  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
ROM: What do you think?

2
00:00:02.878 --> 00:00:03.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LEETA: I don't know.

3
00:00:04.557 --> 00:00:05.557  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you think?

4
00:00:06.597 --> 00:00:07.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I like it.

5
00:00:09.636 --> 00:00:10.916  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't you?

6
00:00:10.995 --> 00:00:13.515  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Rom, it's two handkerchiefs
and a loincloth.

7
00:00:14.436 --> 00:00:16.085  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I suppose we could lose the handkerchiefs.

8
00:00:17.353 --> 00:00:21.444  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ferengi tradition or no Ferengi tradition,
I am not going to be naked at my wedding.

9
00:00:21.515 --> 00:00:22.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who said anything about naked?

10
00:00:23.473 --> 00:00:25.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You'll still have the loincloth.

11
00:00:27.551 --> 00:00:28.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Please show us something else.

12
00:00:29.032 --> 00:00:30.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There is nothing else.

13
00:00:30.731 --> 00:00:33.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've shown you 153
different wedding dresses,

14
00:00:33.612 --> 00:00:36.873  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
from Tellarite modern
to Risian traditional,

15
00:00:36.873 --> 00:00:38.102  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and you've hated them all.

16
00:00:38.312 --> 00:00:41.191  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I like number 38.

17
00:00:41.272 --> 00:00:42.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Number 38?

18
00:00:42.707 --> 00:00:45.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It had more layers
than a Baduviam tapestry.

19
00:00:45.606 --> 00:00:47.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It was elegant.
-It was bulky.

20
00:00:48.306 --> 00:00:49.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I liked 64.

21
00:00:50.145 --> 00:00:52.025  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Sixty-four?
-( exclaims in disgust )

22
00:00:52.025 --> 00:00:53.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, at least they agree on something.

23
00:00:55.264 --> 00:00:57.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why don't you just let Garak
design a dress on his own?

24
00:00:59.062 --> 00:01:01.302  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know whatever he comes up with
will be beautiful.

25
00:01:01.302 --> 00:01:05.109  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My dear, I find your blind adoration
both flattering and disturbing.

26
00:01:05.421 --> 00:01:06.782  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But she does have a point.

27
00:01:06.980 --> 00:01:07.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
QUARK: Leeta!

28
00:01:07.980 --> 00:01:10.699  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That 15-minute break you asked for
was up an hour ago.

29
00:01:10.699 --> 00:01:12.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Brother, what do you think of this dress?

30
00:01:14.572 --> 00:01:16.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't want to think about it.

31
00:01:16.897 --> 00:01:18.798  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All I know is that any marriage

32
00:01:18.798 --> 00:01:23.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
where the female is allowed to speak
and wear clothing is doomed to failure.

33
00:01:25.874 --> 00:01:27.655  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your dabo table awaits.

34
00:01:28.394 --> 00:01:29.393  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( exclaims angrily )

35
00:01:30.873 --> 00:01:31.752  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There he is.

36
00:01:33.392 --> 00:01:34.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's talk to him.

37
00:01:35.649 --> 00:01:36.311  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now?

38
00:01:36.671 --> 00:01:38.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, Rom.

39
00:01:38.610 --> 00:01:40.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Keiko and the kids
will be a lot safer on Earth

40
00:01:40.551 --> 00:01:41.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
than they are here.

41
00:01:42.249 --> 00:01:44.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They've only been gone two days,
and I miss them already.

42
00:01:45.189 --> 00:01:47.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Still, don't you feel better
knowing they're out of harm's way?

43
00:01:48.964 --> 00:01:51.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I wish I could convince Jake
to visit Earth for a while.

44
00:01:51.067 --> 00:01:53.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain. Can we speak to you for a moment?

45
00:01:53.648 --> 00:01:54.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you're not too busy.

46
00:01:54.865 --> 00:01:56.005  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh. Go ahead.

47
00:01:58.264 --> 00:01:59.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Would you marry me?

48
00:02:00.424 --> 00:02:01.784  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean us.

49
00:02:01.943 --> 00:02:06.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I mean, would you perform
our wedding ceremony?

50
00:02:07.255 --> 00:02:09.517  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It would be a great honor
to be married by the Emissary.

51
00:02:09.682 --> 00:02:13.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's not for another two weeks,
so you have plenty of time to get ready.

52
00:02:14.000 --> 00:02:16.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I guess I'll have to start
brushing up on my Bajoran.

53
00:02:17.638 --> 00:02:18.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Me, too.

54
00:02:19.239 --> 00:02:21.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Captain?
-If you'll excuse me?

55
00:02:29.556 --> 00:02:31.074  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe they're not coming.

56
00:02:31.074 --> 00:02:32.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That would be a nice surprise.

57
00:02:39.263 --> 00:02:41.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
One thing I'll say for the Dominion...
they're punctual.

58
00:02:43.271 --> 00:02:45.332  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's the fifth convoy
headed for Cardassia

59
00:02:45.332 --> 00:02:46.332  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in the last five weeks.

60
00:02:47.329 --> 00:02:50.071  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can only imagine how many Jem'Hadar
soldiers are stationed there now.

61
00:02:50.071 --> 00:02:50.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Too many.

62
00:02:52.881 --> 00:02:54.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I wish they'd just attack
and get it over with.

63
00:02:55.767 --> 00:02:57.747  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have the feeling you're
going to get your wish.

64
00:04:54.731 --> 00:04:57.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks for the invite, Dad.

65
00:04:57.526 --> 00:05:00.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I haven't had a home-cooked meal since--
-Since the last time you were here.

66
00:05:01.810 --> 00:05:03.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Sounds about right.

67
00:05:03.409 --> 00:05:04.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
So, uh, what's for dinner?

68
00:05:06.817 --> 00:05:09.486  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Ah. Can I get some salsa with that?

69
00:05:09.567 --> 00:05:10.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Read the headline.

70
00:05:11.846 --> 00:05:14.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
"Bajorans Continue Negotiations
with Dominion."

71
00:05:15.045 --> 00:05:15.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Go on.

72
00:05:17.184 --> 00:05:19.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
"Station Commander
Opposes Nonaggression Pact."

73
00:05:19.764 --> 00:05:20.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
And the byline.

74
00:05:23.043 --> 00:05:24.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
"By Jake Sisko."

75
00:05:27.682 --> 00:05:29.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You should have warned me.

76
00:05:30.321 --> 00:05:31.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I was waiting for the right moment.

77
00:05:31.541 --> 00:05:33.922  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The right moment was before
you published the article.

78
00:05:34.340 --> 00:05:36.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I know. I'm sorry.

79
00:05:37.242 --> 00:05:38.462  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
But aren't you glad I got a job?

80
00:05:39.174 --> 00:05:40.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You mean, this isn't a one-time thing?

81
00:05:41.278 --> 00:05:44.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Nope. I'm now an official correspondent
for the Starfleet News Service.

82
00:05:46.695 --> 00:05:47.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Well, what about your novel?

83
00:05:47.696 --> 00:05:48.756  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I'm not giving up on it,

84
00:05:49.015 --> 00:05:51.031  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
but, this way,
I get to see my work in print.

85
00:05:51.354 --> 00:05:54.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
And, apparently, I get to see
everything I say in print, too.

86
00:05:54.374 --> 00:05:56.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
( scoffs ) You're a public figure, Dad.

87
00:05:57.113 --> 00:05:59.314  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You're the Captain
of the most important space station

88
00:05:59.552 --> 00:06:00.832  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
in the entire Federation.

89
00:06:00.912 --> 00:06:01.951  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You're news.

90
00:06:02.032 --> 00:06:03.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Don't remind me.

91
00:06:09.150 --> 00:06:11.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I guess I can't stop you
from doing your job.

92
00:06:12.189 --> 00:06:13.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can I quote you on that?

93
00:06:14.987 --> 00:06:18.125  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
( clears throat softly ) I guess not.

94
00:06:20.546 --> 00:06:22.026  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Yamok sauce.

95
00:06:22.405 --> 00:06:23.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Who would bother to smuggle in

96
00:06:24.245 --> 00:06:27.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
10,000 wrappages
of Cardassian yamok sauce?

97
00:06:28.484 --> 00:06:30.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Oh. Quark.

98
00:06:30.324 --> 00:06:31.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
That little worm.

99
00:06:31.722 --> 00:06:33.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
He thinks the Cardassians
are going to retake the station.

100
00:06:33.454 --> 00:06:35.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
He's a Ferengi.
You can't blame him for hedging his bets.

101
00:06:36.461 --> 00:06:38.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
But it is a lot of yamok sauce.

102
00:06:39.540 --> 00:06:40.861  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
What is a yamok, anyway?

103
00:06:42.144 --> 00:06:43.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
What would you like me to do with it?

104
00:06:46.647 --> 00:06:47.063  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Major?

105
00:06:47.663 --> 00:06:49.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't care. You decide.

106
00:06:50.502 --> 00:06:51.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dump it.

107
00:06:52.181 --> 00:06:53.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Very good.

108
00:06:56.300 --> 00:06:58.020  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Would you mind telling me what's going on?

109
00:06:58.100 --> 00:07:00.339  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-What do you mean?
-You and Odo.

110
00:07:00.419 --> 00:07:01.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
You've been avoiding each other for weeks.

111
00:07:02.193 --> 00:07:04.538  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-Oh, it's a long story.
-Those are the best kind.

112
00:07:06.183 --> 00:07:09.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighing ) Odo has... feelings for me.

113
00:07:10.751 --> 00:07:13.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What kind of feelings?
-The kind that aren't easy to talk about.

114
00:07:14.390 --> 00:07:15.930  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Since when?

115
00:07:15.930 --> 00:07:17.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Since, I don't know-- years.

116
00:07:17.361 --> 00:07:18.706  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I just found out about it last month.

117
00:07:19.279 --> 00:07:20.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That explains a lot.

118
00:07:20.548 --> 00:07:22.609  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It does?
-Not really.

119
00:07:23.248 --> 00:07:25.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It just seemed
like the right thing to say.

120
00:07:27.666 --> 00:07:29.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I had no idea.
-Neither did I.

121
00:07:33.744 --> 00:07:36.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
60 degrees Celsius--
just the way you like it.

122
00:07:40.942 --> 00:07:42.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, sir...

123
00:07:42.702 --> 00:07:45.381  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is it true what they're saying
about the Romulans?

124
00:07:45.770 --> 00:07:46.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do they say?

125
00:07:47.283 --> 00:07:50.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, there were some Orion Free Traders
in Quark's last night,

126
00:07:50.940 --> 00:07:52.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and they heard from a Vulcan diplomat

127
00:07:52.340 --> 00:07:53.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that the Romulans

128
00:07:53.670 --> 00:07:55.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
signed a nonaggression pact
with the Dominion.

129
00:07:56.426 --> 00:07:58.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A lot of rumors float around
at a time like this, Cadet.

130
00:07:59.809 --> 00:08:01.948  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just don't forget
the 190th Rule of Acquisition.

131
00:08:03.864 --> 00:08:04.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"Hear all, trust nothing."

132
00:08:05.914 --> 00:08:06.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good advice, sir.

133
00:08:15.952 --> 00:08:17.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Romulans.

134
00:08:19.889 --> 00:08:20.549  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sisko to Dax.

135
00:08:20.810 --> 00:08:21.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Dax here.</i>

136
00:08:22.229 --> 00:08:24.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Put me through to Starfleet Intelligence.

137
00:08:25.709 --> 00:08:26.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Romulans!

138
00:08:26.810 --> 00:08:28.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I always knew they were without honor!

139
00:08:28.909 --> 00:08:29.909  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now they have proven it.

140
00:08:29.989 --> 00:08:31.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When did they sign the treaty?

141
00:08:31.549 --> 00:08:34.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yesterday. They must
be desperate to side with the Dominion.

142
00:08:34.389 --> 00:08:36.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Technically,
they're not siding with anyone.

143
00:08:36.110 --> 00:08:37.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's a nonaggression pact.

144
00:08:37.350 --> 00:08:40.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Which means if the Dominion attacks,
they just sit by and do nothing.

145
00:08:40.590 --> 00:08:43.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Romulans,
the Miradorn, the Tholians...

146
00:08:44.149 --> 00:08:47.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the Dominion is making impressive inroads
in the Alpha Quadrant.

147
00:08:47.669 --> 00:08:49.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And the Bajorans are
still talking to them?

148
00:08:50.049 --> 00:08:53.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My people will never sign that treaty
or any other agreement with the Dominion.

149
00:08:53.509 --> 00:08:56.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Meanwhile, more Jem'Hadar ships
come through the wormhole every week.

150
00:08:56.629 --> 00:08:57.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It must stop.

151
00:08:57.789 --> 00:08:58.889  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's going to stop.

152
00:09:00.129 --> 00:09:01.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've talked to Starfleet Command.

153
00:09:02.149 --> 00:09:05.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They've agreed that no more Dominion ships
can be allowed into the Alpha Quadrant.

154
00:09:05.829 --> 00:09:06.909  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How do we keep them out?

155
00:09:06.970 --> 00:09:09.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're going to mine
the entrance to the wormhole.

156
00:09:09.509 --> 00:09:13.049  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Prevent the Dominion from bringing
any more reinforcements to Cardassia.

157
00:09:13.209 --> 00:09:16.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If we try to stop those convoys,
it may very well start a war.

158
00:09:16.669 --> 00:09:17.889  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe so...

159
00:09:18.889 --> 00:09:20.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but one thing is certain.

160
00:09:20.269 --> 00:09:21.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're losing the peace,

161
00:09:21.809 --> 00:09:25.669  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
which means a war could be our only hope.

162
00:09:33.468 --> 00:09:34.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about pulse mines?

163
00:09:35.068 --> 00:09:37.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We could equip them
with variable geometry detonators.

164
00:09:38.147 --> 00:09:39.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) Not good enough.

165
00:09:39.017 --> 00:09:40.913  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Dominion ships can wait
at the mouth of the wormhole

166
00:09:40.913 --> 00:09:42.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and pick them off one by one.

167
00:09:42.456 --> 00:09:43.455  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What if we cloaked them?

168
00:09:43.832 --> 00:09:45.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Cloaking doesn't always work
against the Dominion.

169
00:09:45.904 --> 00:09:48.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe cloaked ships don't,
but I'm thinking much smaller...

170
00:09:49.504 --> 00:09:51.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
each mine no more than a meter across.

171
00:09:52.943 --> 00:09:56.010  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, mines that small
don't have a lot of power.

172
00:09:56.010 --> 00:09:58.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It would take dozens of them
to disable a warship.

173
00:09:59.729 --> 00:10:02.408  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'd run out of mines
before they ran out of ships.

174
00:10:03.248 --> 00:10:05.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rom! Are you here?

175
00:10:05.998 --> 00:10:09.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"Cloak. Small. Dozens."
I heard every word.

176
00:10:09.757 --> 00:10:12.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, something's wrong.
You haven't touched your food.

177
00:10:12.216 --> 00:10:13.416  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's my stomach.

178
00:10:13.696 --> 00:10:15.837  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ever since Captain Sisko agreed
to officiate at our wedding,

179
00:10:16.256 --> 00:10:17.396  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I haven't had much of an appetite.

180
00:10:17.595 --> 00:10:19.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought you wanted
Captain Sisko to marry you.

181
00:10:20.275 --> 00:10:23.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I did, but now that he said yes,
it's become so...

182
00:10:25.672 --> 00:10:26.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
real.

183
00:10:29.112 --> 00:10:30.591  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm going to get married!

184
00:10:30.671 --> 00:10:33.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not for another two weeks,
and in the meantime, we have work to do.

185
00:10:33.750 --> 00:10:35.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But what if Leeta turns out
to be just like Nog's mother?

186
00:10:36.129 --> 00:10:37.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What if I can't make her happy?

187
00:10:37.809 --> 00:10:39.249  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What if this is
the biggest mistake of my life?

188
00:10:39.329 --> 00:10:40.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What if--
-Rom!

189
00:10:44.847 --> 00:10:46.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Self-replication.

190
00:10:46.927 --> 00:10:48.206  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's the only answer.

191
00:10:49.165 --> 00:10:50.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Self-replication?

192
00:10:50.685 --> 00:10:53.266  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If the mines are going to be small,
we'll need a lot of them,

193
00:10:53.604 --> 00:10:55.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and we'll need a way
to replace them quickly

194
00:10:55.484 --> 00:10:57.785  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
if the Jem'Hadar try to blast
their way through, and...

195
00:10:58.722 --> 00:11:01.402  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh-oh. I forgot to request new quarters.

196
00:11:01.881 --> 00:11:02.762  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mine are too small.

197
00:11:02.841 --> 00:11:04.401  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where are Leeta and I going to live?

198
00:11:04.481 --> 00:11:05.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rom, I think you're on to something.

199
00:11:05.960 --> 00:11:07.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know I am.
I've measured them three times.

200
00:11:08.080 --> 00:11:09.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's nowhere to put her prayer mandala.

201
00:11:09.559 --> 00:11:11.720  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We could equip each mine
with a replicator unit.

202
00:11:11.899 --> 00:11:13.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No matter how many
the Jem'Hadar destroyed,

203
00:11:13.620 --> 00:11:14.540  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
there'd always be more.

204
00:11:14.678 --> 00:11:17.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We'd program them to swarm detonate...
20 or 30 mines to each ship.

205
00:11:18.317 --> 00:11:19.858  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The only problem is you'll have to wait

206
00:11:19.858 --> 00:11:22.288  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
until the entire mine field
is deployed before you activate it.

207
00:11:22.635 --> 00:11:25.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Otherwise, the proximity sensors
could cause premature detonation.

208
00:11:27.234 --> 00:11:29.233  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Where's Leeta going to put
all her clothes?

209
00:11:29.613 --> 00:11:31.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't have enough closet space.

210
00:11:31.713 --> 00:11:34.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I better go talk to Sisko.
-I'll go draw up some specs.

211
00:11:34.512 --> 00:11:37.071  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've got to go to waste extraction.

212
00:11:37.711 --> 00:11:39.430  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What did Starfleet Command say?

213
00:11:39.510 --> 00:11:41.110  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How many reinforcements
will they be sending?

214
00:11:41.190 --> 00:11:42.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
KIRA: And how soon will they get here?

215
00:11:42.710 --> 00:11:44.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're not getting any reinforcements.

216
00:11:44.589 --> 00:11:46.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll have to make do with what we've got.

217
00:11:47.568 --> 00:11:48.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What we've got isn't enough.

218
00:11:48.928 --> 00:11:50.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sir, as Strategic Operations Officer,

219
00:11:50.809 --> 00:11:52.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I cannot guarantee
the safety of this station

220
00:11:52.688 --> 00:11:54.048  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
if the Dominion fleet attacks.

221
00:11:54.486 --> 00:11:55.827  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your concerns are noted, Commander.

222
00:11:56.205 --> 00:11:57.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's Starfleet thinking?

223
00:11:58.325 --> 00:12:01.044  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They must have given you a reason
for denying your request.

224
00:12:01.124 --> 00:12:02.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-They did.
-And?

225
00:12:03.203 --> 00:12:04.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not at liberty to discuss it.

226
00:12:05.643 --> 00:12:07.042  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's just say

227
00:12:07.042 --> 00:12:09.513  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Starfleet's resources
will be needed elsewhere.

228
00:12:09.922 --> 00:12:12.241  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What could be more important
than defending this station?

229
00:12:12.241 --> 00:12:13.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That is not for us to decide.

230
00:12:14.100 --> 00:12:15.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are our orders, Captain?

231
00:12:15.820 --> 00:12:18.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Deploy the minefield and prepare
for a Dominion attack.

232
00:12:18.401 --> 00:12:19.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And when the attack comes?

233
00:12:19.878 --> 00:12:21.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then we are to defend the station

234
00:12:21.558 --> 00:12:24.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
until the mines are in position
and the field has been activated.

235
00:12:24.328 --> 00:12:27.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The <i>Defiant </i>will be unable
to raise shields or cloak

236
00:12:27.296 --> 00:12:28.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
while deploying the mines.

237
00:12:28.330 --> 00:12:29.053  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She will be an easy target.

238
00:12:29.074 --> 00:12:31.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then it's up to DS9 to defend her.

239
00:12:32.315 --> 00:12:35.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If the Dominion wants to stop the <i>Defiant,</i>
they'll have to come through us.

240
00:12:40.912 --> 00:12:42.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You wanted to see me, Constable?

241
00:12:43.032 --> 00:12:44.791  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Major, I'd like your permission

242
00:12:44.831 --> 00:12:47.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to terminate all outgoing
subspace communications.

243
00:12:48.909 --> 00:12:50.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You really think that's necessary?

244
00:12:50.969 --> 00:12:52.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is no time for security leaks.

245
00:12:53.069 --> 00:12:57.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've prepared a number of false messages
we can transmit at random intervals

246
00:12:57.852 --> 00:13:01.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so there won't be any noticeable drop
in our outgoing subspace traffic.

247
00:13:01.706 --> 00:13:02.726  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll see what I can do.

248
00:13:04.428 --> 00:13:05.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd appreciate that.

249
00:13:06.985 --> 00:13:07.385  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Major...

250
00:13:10.264 --> 00:13:11.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

251
00:13:14.842 --> 00:13:16.443  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's something you ought to know.

252
00:13:17.412 --> 00:13:18.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's that?

253
00:13:19.920 --> 00:13:23.402  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been thinking about
asking you out to dinner.

254
00:13:31.357 --> 00:13:33.316  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've been expecting something like this.

255
00:13:33.716 --> 00:13:34.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I could tell.

256
00:13:36.196 --> 00:13:38.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You've looked a little uncomfortable
around me lately.

257
00:13:38.994 --> 00:13:41.234  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, you've looked
a little uncomfortable yourself.

258
00:13:43.365 --> 00:13:45.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Which is why I wanted you to know
I'm not going to do it.

259
00:13:46.872 --> 00:13:48.573  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No dinner invitations, no flowers,

260
00:13:48.573 --> 00:13:50.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
no attempts at changing the nature
of our relationship.

261
00:13:52.411 --> 00:13:55.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Until the current crisis has passed,
we both need our minds to be clear,

262
00:13:55.533 --> 00:13:58.042  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to be free of any
unnecessary distractions.

263
00:13:59.333 --> 00:14:00.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that's probably a good idea.

264
00:14:02.848 --> 00:14:05.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So for now,
all we need to concern ourselves with

265
00:14:05.470 --> 00:14:08.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is deploying the minefield,
maintaining station security,

266
00:14:08.550 --> 00:14:10.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and preparing ourselves
for a possible invasion.

267
00:14:10.829 --> 00:14:11.869  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm...

268
00:14:13.508 --> 00:14:15.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I don't know about you...

269
00:14:16.484 --> 00:14:18.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but I feel more comfortable already.

270
00:14:19.923 --> 00:14:21.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

271
00:14:21.802 --> 00:14:23.122  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckles )

272
00:14:25.041 --> 00:14:28.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
SISKO: <i>Captain's Log, Stardate 50975.2.</i>

273
00:14:28.880 --> 00:14:31.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The next Jem'Hadar convoy </i>
<i>is due in five days,</i>

274
00:14:32.139 --> 00:14:33.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>but our efforts to mine the wormhole</i>

275
00:14:34.078 --> 00:14:36.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>have already provoked</i>
<i>a response from the Dominion,</i>

276
00:14:37.237 --> 00:14:38.946  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>who have sent </i>
<i>their Vorta ambassador, Weyoun,</i>

277
00:14:39.797 --> 00:14:40.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>to speak with me.</i>

278
00:14:44.013 --> 00:14:45.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What can I do for you, Weyoun?

279
00:14:45.955 --> 00:14:47.914  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Captain Sisko...

280
00:14:48.535 --> 00:14:50.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll make this brief.

281
00:14:51.429 --> 00:14:52.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We know all about the mine field.

282
00:14:53.473 --> 00:14:55.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I assumed you'd find out sooner or later.

283
00:14:56.431 --> 00:14:58.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As I see it, you have two choices.

284
00:14:59.590 --> 00:15:01.590  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Either you remove the mines,

285
00:15:01.670 --> 00:15:04.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
or we will take this station from you

286
00:15:05.669 --> 00:15:07.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and remove them ourselves.

287
00:15:13.907 --> 00:15:15.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I appreciate your directness.

288
00:15:16.545 --> 00:15:17.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, let me be direct with you.

289
00:15:18.644 --> 00:15:19.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The mines stay.

290
00:15:20.522 --> 00:15:21.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will not allow any more

291
00:15:21.843 --> 00:15:24.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Dominion reinforcements
through the wormhole.

292
00:15:24.183 --> 00:15:26.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You will not allow?
-You heard me.

293
00:15:30.175 --> 00:15:32.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can see how that might be
your first reaction.

294
00:15:33.359 --> 00:15:37.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But you and I are reasonable men.

295
00:15:38.204 --> 00:15:39.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And surely, reasonable men can come

296
00:15:39.692 --> 00:15:42.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to some sort of
mutually acceptable compromise.

297
00:15:42.358 --> 00:15:44.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I didn't think the Dominion
believed in compromise.

298
00:15:45.077 --> 00:15:46.877  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

299
00:15:46.877 --> 00:15:50.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It saddens me to see how deeply
you misunderstand us.

300
00:15:51.151 --> 00:15:51.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All the Dominion wants

301
00:15:51.915 --> 00:15:54.116  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is to peacefully coexist
with its neighbors.

302
00:15:54.514 --> 00:15:56.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then why the continued military buildup?

303
00:15:56.634 --> 00:15:59.716  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why the weekly convoys of ships and troops
from the Gamma Quadrant?

304
00:16:02.871 --> 00:16:04.831  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's the Cardassians.

305
00:16:04.831 --> 00:16:06.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't get me wrong.

306
00:16:06.431 --> 00:16:08.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm pleased to call them allies,

307
00:16:08.230 --> 00:16:11.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but as you know, they've just been through
a terrible war with the Klingons.

308
00:16:11.032 --> 00:16:14.077  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid it's left them
somewhat jittery,

309
00:16:14.468 --> 00:16:17.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
so they're understandably
concerned about ensuring

310
00:16:17.290 --> 00:16:18.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the sovereignty of their borders.

311
00:16:18.849 --> 00:16:20.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And since they're now
members of the Dominion,

312
00:16:21.066 --> 00:16:23.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
their concerns have become our concerns.

313
00:16:24.425 --> 00:16:25.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I would think by now

314
00:16:25.466 --> 00:16:28.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you have more than enough ships
to defend Cardassia.

315
00:16:28.345 --> 00:16:31.144  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You may think that, and I may think that,
but the Cardassians--

316
00:16:31.425 --> 00:16:33.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, yes, I know. They're jittery.

317
00:16:33.504 --> 00:16:34.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You see our dilemma.

318
00:16:36.183 --> 00:16:37.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm beginning to.

319
00:16:39.701 --> 00:16:40.941  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What if...

320
00:16:42.319 --> 00:16:46.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we agreed to limit our
convoys to cargo ships,

321
00:16:46.638 --> 00:16:48.316  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
construction units, civilian aid?

322
00:16:48.478 --> 00:16:50.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Things that will help them get
their economy back on its feet.

323
00:16:51.686 --> 00:16:55.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Did you know when we arrived
children were starving on Cardassia Prime?

324
00:16:56.577 --> 00:16:57.596  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was heartbreaking.

325
00:16:58.416 --> 00:17:01.055  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I had no idea things were so bad.

326
00:17:02.234 --> 00:17:04.415  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Cardassians are a very proud people.

327
00:17:04.415 --> 00:17:07.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They don't want to admit to outsiders
how dire the situation really is.

328
00:17:09.734 --> 00:17:11.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So...

329
00:17:11.462 --> 00:17:12.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
are we agreed?

330
00:17:13.351 --> 00:17:14.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You remove the mines,

331
00:17:14.990 --> 00:17:17.892  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and we restrict our convoys
to medical and economic assistance.

332
00:17:18.169 --> 00:17:19.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That sounds reasonable.

333
00:17:20.368 --> 00:17:22.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'd have to discuss it
with Starfleet first, of course.

334
00:17:23.684 --> 00:17:26.644  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sure they'll do whatever
Benjamin Sisko recommends.

335
00:17:26.665 --> 00:17:29.664  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
For my part,
I'll personally speak to the Founders

336
00:17:29.745 --> 00:17:31.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to secure our end of the bargain.

337
00:17:31.264 --> 00:17:33.024  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about Gul Dukat?

338
00:17:33.606 --> 00:17:35.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, he'll be furious...

339
00:17:36.643 --> 00:17:37.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
at first.

340
00:17:38.523 --> 00:17:41.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But we've developed
a fine working relationship,

341
00:17:41.165 --> 00:17:44.465  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I'm sure I can help him
to see the wisdom of our decision.

342
00:17:45.241 --> 00:17:47.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will leave it in your capable hands.

343
00:17:48.520 --> 00:17:49.901  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You won't be disappointed.

344
00:17:56.318 --> 00:17:57.878  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is a momentous day.

345
00:17:57.957 --> 00:18:00.116  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You and I have just taken the first step

346
00:18:00.197 --> 00:18:03.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
towards insuring peace
between our peoples.

347
00:18:12.402 --> 00:18:13.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're going to attack.

348
00:18:13.793 --> 00:18:15.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Are you sure?
-I am positive.

349
00:18:15.792 --> 00:18:18.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The moment I mentioned
that we weren't going to remove the mines,

350
00:18:18.283 --> 00:18:19.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
we both knew there'd be war.

351
00:18:19.670 --> 00:18:20.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Everything else was just words...

352
00:18:21.130 --> 00:18:24.172  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
a feeble attempt to lull the other side
into a false sense of security.

353
00:18:24.269 --> 00:18:26.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I didn't buy it,
and I'm sure Weyoun didn't either.

354
00:18:26.490 --> 00:18:27.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How soon?

355
00:18:28.048 --> 00:18:29.909  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As soon as they can get
their fleet from Cardassia.

356
00:18:30.127 --> 00:18:31.487  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd say as early as tomorrow.

357
00:18:32.227 --> 00:18:34.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Which means we have to finish
the minefield today.

358
00:18:35.386 --> 00:18:36.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We need more time.</i>

359
00:18:36.986 --> 00:18:37.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You don't have it.

360
00:18:38.225 --> 00:18:40.984  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We'll do the best we can. Dax out.</i>

361
00:18:41.764 --> 00:18:44.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
General, take your ship
and patrol the border.

362
00:18:44.426 --> 00:18:46.015  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
At the first sight
of the Dominion ships...

363
00:18:46.203 --> 00:18:47.564  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will sound the alarm.

364
00:18:47.564 --> 00:18:48.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't engage the enemy.

365
00:18:49.362 --> 00:18:50.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Get back to the station
as soon as you can.

366
00:18:50.843 --> 00:18:51.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're going to need you here.

367
00:18:51.901 --> 00:18:55.363  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Captain, fighting them at the border
or fighting them here at the station

368
00:18:55.363 --> 00:18:56.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
makes no difference to me.

369
00:18:59.012 --> 00:19:01.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You don't think
Starfleet could be persuaded

370
00:19:00.602 --> 00:19:03.599  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to send us a few more ships, say 50?

371
00:19:03.690 --> 00:19:05.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm afraid not, Doctor. We're on our own.

372
00:19:05.336 --> 00:19:07.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In that case, I'd better go
and get the infirmary ready.

373
00:19:09.654 --> 00:19:12.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Mr. Worf, see to the weapons array
and issue combat assignments.

374
00:19:13.053 --> 00:19:14.293  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aye, sir.

375
00:19:15.494 --> 00:19:15.894  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Major.

376
00:19:16.333 --> 00:19:18.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll contact the Bajoran Militia,
see if they can spare a few ships.

377
00:19:18.955 --> 00:19:19.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Forget the Militia.

378
00:19:20.253 --> 00:19:22.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I need you to contact
the Council of Ministers.

379
00:19:22.094 --> 00:19:23.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Tell them I need to meet
with them immediately.

380
00:19:23.654 --> 00:19:26.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As a Starfleet Captain
or as the Emissary of the Prophets?

381
00:19:27.053 --> 00:19:28.053  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Both.

382
00:19:28.132 --> 00:19:29.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That'll get their attention.

383
00:19:29.252 --> 00:19:30.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Remember the nonaggression pact

384
00:19:30.611 --> 00:19:32.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the Dominion offered Bajor
a few weeks ago?

385
00:19:32.649 --> 00:19:34.770  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah, they're still debating it
in the Council of Ministers.

386
00:19:34.770 --> 00:19:35.694  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It'll never pass.

387
00:19:35.908 --> 00:19:38.249  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It'll pass if the Emissary endorses it.

388
00:19:39.147 --> 00:19:41.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You want Bajor to sign a treaty
with the Dominion?

389
00:19:42.866 --> 00:19:44.065  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why?

390
00:19:45.545 --> 00:19:46.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Major, when I came here,

391
00:19:46.645 --> 00:19:48.246  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
my orders were to protect Bajor

392
00:19:48.396 --> 00:19:50.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and help your people
rebuild from the Occupation.

393
00:19:50.743 --> 00:19:51.623  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've succeeded.

394
00:19:51.963 --> 00:19:54.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And I refuse to see everything
we've accomplished torn down again.

395
00:19:57.041 --> 00:20:00.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The sad truth is, Major,
if there is a war now,

396
00:20:01.141 --> 00:20:03.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the Federation can't guarantee
the safety of Bajor,

397
00:20:04.485 --> 00:20:07.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
which means Bajor must
be kept out of the fighting.

398
00:20:08.278 --> 00:20:10.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't like this
any more than you do, Major,

399
00:20:11.457 --> 00:20:13.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but it's Bajor's only chance for survival.

400
00:20:15.948 --> 00:20:17.357  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
SISKO: <i>Captain's Log, supplemental.</i>

401
00:20:17.755 --> 00:20:19.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Bajor has signed the nonaggression pact</i>
<i>with the Dominion.</i>

402
00:20:20.155 --> 00:20:22.777  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>All Bajoran personnel have been ordered</i>
<i>to evacuate the station.</i>

403
00:20:23.033 --> 00:20:24.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>As someone once said,</i>

404
00:20:24.393 --> 00:20:27.115  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>"These are the times </i>
<i>that try men's souls."</i>

405
00:20:27.912 --> 00:20:29.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
ZIYAL: Are you sure you
won't come with me?

406
00:20:29.312 --> 00:20:31.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
GARAK: I don't think I'd be
very welcome on Bajor.

407
00:20:31.711 --> 00:20:33.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not going to be
very popular there, either.

408
00:20:33.631 --> 00:20:35.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My dear, you're half-Bajoran.

409
00:20:35.101 --> 00:20:37.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So at least half of you
is going to be accepted.

410
00:20:37.890 --> 00:20:40.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sure that Major Kira's friends
will take good care of you.

411
00:20:42.088 --> 00:20:43.768  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, what's going to happen to you?

412
00:20:43.768 --> 00:20:45.179  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, well, let me tell you a story.

413
00:20:45.780 --> 00:20:47.021  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I once knew a Cardassian,

414
00:20:47.021 --> 00:20:50.046  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
a dashing, handsome young man
with a promising career.

415
00:20:50.266 --> 00:20:52.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But one day, through no fault of his own,

416
00:20:52.425 --> 00:20:55.467  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
he found himself exiled and alone
with nowhere to turn.

417
00:20:55.744 --> 00:20:57.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But did he give up?

418
00:20:57.744 --> 00:20:59.063  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

419
00:20:59.521 --> 00:21:01.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He struck upon a brilliant plan.

420
00:21:02.222 --> 00:21:04.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Instead of fleeing
for the rest of his life,

421
00:21:04.701 --> 00:21:05.702  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
he sought shelter

422
00:21:05.702 --> 00:21:08.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
in the one place no one
expected him to go...

423
00:21:09.180 --> 00:21:12.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
in a stronghold of his
people's most hated enemies.

424
00:21:12.739 --> 00:21:16.001  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There, surrounded by hostile strangers,
he built a life.

425
00:21:16.118 --> 00:21:18.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And there, against all odds,

426
00:21:18.379 --> 00:21:21.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
against the merciless logic
of the universe itself,

427
00:21:22.976 --> 00:21:23.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
he thrived.

428
00:21:24.535 --> 00:21:27.277  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
By becoming the greatest tailor
in the galaxy.

429
00:21:27.801 --> 00:21:29.352  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And the moral of the story, my dear,

430
00:21:30.194 --> 00:21:34.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is to never underestimate
my gift for survival.

431
00:21:55.506 --> 00:21:58.067  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( speaking native language )

432
00:22:08.142 --> 00:22:09.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You may kiss the bride.

433
00:22:14.261 --> 00:22:16.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Congratulations, Father.

434
00:22:17.739 --> 00:22:19.339  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh... Moogie.

435
00:22:19.899 --> 00:22:21.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you, Nog.

436
00:22:22.698 --> 00:22:25.640  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, if you'll excuse me,
I have business to attend to.

437
00:22:31.196 --> 00:22:36.339  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, that was the most pathetic excuse
for a wedding ceremony I've ever seen.

438
00:22:37.844 --> 00:22:40.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No bridal auction, no latinum dances,

439
00:22:40.326 --> 00:22:41.419  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and the bride...

440
00:22:41.432 --> 00:22:43.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the bride was severely overdressed.

441
00:22:43.926 --> 00:22:47.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Nevertheless, you're very happy for us,
aren't you, Brother?

442
00:22:48.570 --> 00:22:49.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Overjoyed.

443
00:22:58.405 --> 00:22:58.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

444
00:23:00.527 --> 00:23:02.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I give it two months.

445
00:23:05.365 --> 00:23:06.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, Rom.

446
00:23:07.085 --> 00:23:08.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No time for that.

447
00:23:08.484 --> 00:23:10.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nog, are Leeta's bags packed?

448
00:23:10.364 --> 00:23:11.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're already on the shuttle.

449
00:23:11.643 --> 00:23:13.683  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You mean we're leaving?
-No.

450
00:23:13.801 --> 00:23:14.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're leaving.

451
00:23:14.822 --> 00:23:16.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
First Minister Shakaar was very clear.

452
00:23:16.982 --> 00:23:19.564  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All Bajorans must leave the station
for their own safety.

453
00:23:20.000 --> 00:23:20.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But what about you?

454
00:23:20.940 --> 00:23:23.021  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My job is here, with Chief O'Brien.

455
00:23:23.140 --> 00:23:24.619  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then I'm not going either.

456
00:23:24.699 --> 00:23:26.059  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You see that, Nog?

457
00:23:26.139 --> 00:23:30.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've barely finished saying our vows,
and we're already having our first fight.

458
00:23:30.698 --> 00:23:32.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're really married.

459
00:23:33.716 --> 00:23:34.916  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've got to go, Leeta.

460
00:23:35.476 --> 00:23:37.097  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The problems of two newlyweds

461
00:23:37.156 --> 00:23:40.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
are but a small thread
in the tapestry of galactic events.

462
00:23:40.775 --> 00:23:43.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You might not understand that today,
or even tomorrow,

463
00:23:43.814 --> 00:23:45.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but someday you will.

464
00:23:47.001 --> 00:23:50.132  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So get on that shuttle
and don't look back.

465
00:23:50.852 --> 00:23:53.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nog, take your Moogie to the Docking Ring.

466
00:23:56.369 --> 00:23:58.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nice speech, Dad.

467
00:24:02.608 --> 00:24:04.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I thought so.

468
00:24:06.347 --> 00:24:09.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Computer, what's the status
of program Sisko-1-9-7?

469
00:24:10.694 --> 00:24:12.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
COMPUTER: <i>All necessary modifications</i>
<i>have been completed.</i>

470
00:24:13.225 --> 00:24:16.367  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Program Sisko-1-9-7 </i>
<i>ready for implementation</i>

471
00:24:16.412 --> 00:24:17.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>on your command.</i>

472
00:24:17.304 --> 00:24:19.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
NOG: <i>Ops to Captain Sisko.</i>

473
00:24:19.460 --> 00:24:22.062  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Sir, we're receiving a message</i>
<i>from the Cardassian border.</i>

474
00:24:22.302 --> 00:24:23.381  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>It's General Martok.</i>

475
00:24:26.061 --> 00:24:27.180  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
On screen.

476
00:24:27.260 --> 00:24:28.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aye, sir.

477
00:24:29.660 --> 00:24:31.139  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
MARTOK: <i>Captain, we just detected</i>

478
00:24:31.140 --> 00:24:33.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>a large force of Dominion ships</i>
<i>headed your way.</i>

479
00:24:34.299 --> 00:24:36.777  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>They should be there within the hou--</i>

480
00:24:39.137 --> 00:24:40.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Someone is jamming his transmission.

481
00:24:41.816 --> 00:24:43.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Contact established.</i>

482
00:24:43.736 --> 00:24:44.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
DUKAT: <i>Captain Sisko,</i>

483
00:24:45.495 --> 00:24:47.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I don't suppose </i>
<i>you would like to surrender</i>

484
00:24:47.854 --> 00:24:50.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and avoid unnecessary bloodshed.</i>

485
00:24:52.753 --> 00:24:53.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Absolutely not.

486
00:24:54.712 --> 00:24:55.853  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I was hoping you'd say that.</i>

487
00:25:00.791 --> 00:25:02.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Battle stations.

488
00:25:06.189 --> 00:25:10.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( alarm blaring )

489
00:25:10.188 --> 00:25:10.929  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How much longer?

490
00:25:10.929 --> 00:25:13.070  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Dominion fleet
should be in weapons range in 20 minutes.

491
00:25:13.146 --> 00:25:14.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are all the Bajorans off the station?

492
00:25:14.647 --> 00:25:16.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
NOG: The last transport just left.

493
00:25:17.146 --> 00:25:19.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( sighs ) Let's hope the Dominion honors
the nonaggression pact.

494
00:25:21.324 --> 00:25:23.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Cadet, put me through to the <i>Defiant.</i>

495
00:25:24.043 --> 00:25:24.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, sir.

496
00:25:25.163 --> 00:25:26.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
On screen.

497
00:25:26.802 --> 00:25:28.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Benjamin, I know what you're going to say,

498
00:25:28.922 --> 00:25:30.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but we've got at least
another hour of work

499
00:25:30.562 --> 00:25:32.082  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
before we can activate the minefield.

500
00:25:32.261 --> 00:25:33.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You don't have an hour, old man.</i>

501
00:25:33.800 --> 00:25:36.021  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The Dominion is going to be here</i>
<i>in less than 20 minutes.</i>

502
00:25:36.119 --> 00:25:37.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You're going to be a sitting duck.</i>

503
00:25:37.905 --> 00:25:39.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Then I hope you can buy us some more time.

504
00:25:39.978 --> 00:25:41.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax out.

505
00:25:42.218 --> 00:25:43.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax to O'Brien.

506
00:25:43.797 --> 00:25:45.858  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know, I know. Work faster.

507
00:25:46.477 --> 00:25:49.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
JAKE: A medical tricorder, hypospray,
dermal regenerator,

508
00:25:49.356 --> 00:25:52.195  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and battlefield trauma kit.

509
00:25:52.275 --> 00:25:54.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Medical tricorder, hypospray
dermal regenerator,

510
00:25:55.074 --> 00:25:56.474  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and battlefield trauma kit.

511
00:25:58.073 --> 00:25:59.073  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) That's everyone.

512
00:25:59.153 --> 00:26:00.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now what?

513
00:26:01.713 --> 00:26:04.231  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now we wait...

514
00:26:05.251 --> 00:26:06.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
until the casualties start coming in.

515
00:26:09.130 --> 00:26:10.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you sure you're all right?

516
00:26:11.410 --> 00:26:12.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be fine.

517
00:26:12.769 --> 00:26:14.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Besides, my father
won't let me stay in Ops,

518
00:26:15.118 --> 00:26:16.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and, uh,
I promised the Federation News Service

519
00:26:16.923 --> 00:26:18.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
a firsthand account of the battle.

520
00:26:18.947 --> 00:26:19.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You'll get it.

521
00:26:20.586 --> 00:26:23.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just remember,
Bashir is spelled with an "I."

522
00:26:31.811 --> 00:26:35.513  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I must say, Constable,
I admire your composure.

523
00:26:36.002 --> 00:26:38.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're an island of tranquility
in a sea of chaos.

524
00:26:39.281 --> 00:26:40.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What I am is useless.

525
00:26:41.040 --> 00:26:43.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My entire staff
has been evacuated to Bajor.

526
00:26:43.900 --> 00:26:46.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm not feeling too terribly
useful myself at this moment.

527
00:26:47.278 --> 00:26:50.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But if it'd make you feel any better,
you could always deputize me.

528
00:26:50.478 --> 00:26:51.797  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( scoffs )

529
00:26:51.817 --> 00:26:54.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sure if the Jem'Hadar
board the station,

530
00:26:54.239 --> 00:26:56.059  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you'll make yourself useful.

531
00:26:56.078 --> 00:26:57.678  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's ironic.

532
00:26:58.238 --> 00:27:00.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When the Klingons attacked the station,

533
00:27:00.235 --> 00:27:02.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Gul Dukat and I
were fighting side by side.

534
00:27:02.473 --> 00:27:04.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
At one point, he turned his back to me,

535
00:27:04.334 --> 00:27:09.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I must admit that for a moment,
he made a very tempting target.

536
00:27:10.491 --> 00:27:12.252  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You'd shoot a man in the back?

537
00:27:12.333 --> 00:27:14.012  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, it's the safest way, isn't it?

538
00:27:14.951 --> 00:27:15.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But then I thought,

539
00:27:15.690 --> 00:27:18.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"Well, no, I can't fight
all these Klingons by myself,"

540
00:27:18.869 --> 00:27:19.749  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
so I let him live.

541
00:27:20.428 --> 00:27:21.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And now you regret it.

542
00:27:22.348 --> 00:27:25.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ah, my dear Constable,
before this day is over,

543
00:27:25.867 --> 00:27:28.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
everyone on this station
is going to regret it.

544
00:27:30.129 --> 00:27:30.906  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( device whirring )

545
00:27:30.985 --> 00:27:32.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rom...

546
00:27:33.325 --> 00:27:34.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've always said you were an idiot,

547
00:27:34.666 --> 00:27:36.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I never believed it
more than I do at this moment.

548
00:27:36.906 --> 00:27:38.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Brother, if you want to insult me,
it's going to have to wait till later.

549
00:27:38.825 --> 00:27:39.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm busy.

550
00:27:39.853 --> 00:27:40.783  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Busy doing what?

551
00:27:41.042 --> 00:27:42.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Preparing perimeter defenses
for the attack.

552
00:27:44.081 --> 00:27:47.561  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There are dozens of engineers
that could be doing that.

553
00:27:48.380 --> 00:27:50.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Starfleet engineers.

554
00:27:51.420 --> 00:27:52.699  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hu-mans.

555
00:27:52.779 --> 00:27:54.299  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( device turns off )

556
00:27:54.299 --> 00:27:55.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You should be on Bajor with your new wife.

557
00:27:56.659 --> 00:27:58.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what Leeta said.

558
00:27:58.898 --> 00:28:01.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, she's right. This is not your fight.

559
00:28:01.244 --> 00:28:03.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's not your fight either,
but I don't see you leaving.

560
00:28:03.257 --> 00:28:04.782  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have to look out for my bar.

561
00:28:05.555 --> 00:28:06.736  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I have to look out for you.

562
00:28:07.237 --> 00:28:08.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Me?
-You're my brother.

563
00:28:09.473 --> 00:28:12.195  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whatever happens, we belong together.

564
00:28:16.792 --> 00:28:18.391  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( device starts up )

565
00:28:19.991 --> 00:28:23.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, like I said, you're an idiot.

566
00:28:31.208 --> 00:28:32.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
NOG: On screen, Captain.

567
00:28:32.187 --> 00:28:35.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
General Martok, take a defensive
position near the <i>Defiant.</i>

568
00:28:35.269 --> 00:28:37.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They have to finish deploying those mines
no matter the cost.

569
00:28:37.665 --> 00:28:38.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>And they will.</i>

570
00:28:39.445 --> 00:28:41.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You have my word on it, Captain.</i>

571
00:28:43.764 --> 00:28:45.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Worf, activate the weapons array.

572
00:28:46.003 --> 00:28:47.043  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aye, sir.

573
00:28:56.080 --> 00:28:58.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Captain, as a Major
in the Bajoran Militia,

574
00:28:58.959 --> 00:29:01.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I must officially protest
Starfleet's refusal

575
00:29:01.518 --> 00:29:03.079  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to turn over this station
to my government.

576
00:29:03.079 --> 00:29:04.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Your protest is duly noted.
-Good.

577
00:29:04.910 --> 00:29:06.318  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now that that's over with...

578
00:29:07.110 --> 00:29:09.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kira Nerys reporting for duty.

579
00:29:27.773 --> 00:29:28.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Weapons range in one minute.

580
00:29:30.791 --> 00:29:33.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been waiting for this moment
for five years.

581
00:29:34.910 --> 00:29:36.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
First, we reclaim Terok Nor,

582
00:29:36.988 --> 00:29:39.349  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
then... on to Bajor.

583
00:29:39.568 --> 00:29:40.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's not get ahead of ourselves.

584
00:29:41.186 --> 00:29:43.267  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Or must I remind you
the Dominion just signed

585
00:29:43.267 --> 00:29:44.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
a nonaggression pact with Bajor?

586
00:29:45.125 --> 00:29:46.817  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Dominion might have.

587
00:29:46.885 --> 00:29:47.505  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I never did.

588
00:29:49.184 --> 00:29:51.065  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Dominion will honor its treaty,

589
00:29:51.144 --> 00:29:54.026  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and as a member of the Dominion,
you will honor it as well.

590
00:29:57.421 --> 00:30:00.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where the Dominion leads, I will follow.

591
00:30:00.617 --> 00:30:01.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I never doubted it.

592
00:30:03.019 --> 00:30:06.561  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Attack wings one through five,
head for the <i>Defiant.</i>

593
00:30:07.319 --> 00:30:10.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Remaining ships, target the station.

594
00:30:16.276 --> 00:30:17.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're within weapons range.

595
00:30:17.716 --> 00:30:19.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well...

596
00:30:19.395 --> 00:30:20.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
then by all means...

597
00:30:23.278 --> 00:30:23.953  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fire.

598
00:30:28.993 --> 00:30:31.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Worf, all weapons fire at will.

599
00:30:54.465 --> 00:30:56.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Enemy ships are closing on the <i>Defiant.</i>

600
00:30:56.944 --> 00:30:59.056  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Mr. Worf.
-Got them.

601
00:31:04.923 --> 00:31:07.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( console beeping )
-Sir, the station's shields are holding.

602
00:31:07.764 --> 00:31:08.564  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Impossible.

603
00:31:08.80 --> 00:31:11.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Federation shields have always proven
useless against our weapons.

604
00:31:11.819 --> 00:31:15.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've found it wise to never underestimate
the Federation's technical skill

605
00:31:16.598 --> 00:31:18.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
or Captain Sisko's resourcefulness.

606
00:31:19.464 --> 00:31:21.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damar, bring us around for another pass.

607
00:31:38.938 --> 00:31:40.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chief, how much longer?

608
00:31:40.338 --> 00:31:41.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
O'BRIEN: <i>Just another couple of minutes.</i>

609
00:31:42.009 --> 00:31:44.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Take us to our final set of coordinates.

610
00:31:44.096 --> 00:31:45.177  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Helm, set course--

611
00:31:52.894 --> 00:31:55.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Chief, I'm going to have to take
evasive maneuvers.

612
00:31:56.726 --> 00:31:58.828  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you do, you risk setting off
every mine on this ship.

613
00:31:59.485 --> 00:32:00.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( yells )

614
00:32:01.944 --> 00:32:04.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And if I don't,
we may not have a ship left!

615
00:32:14.660 --> 00:32:16.501  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You may continue your work, Commander.</i>

616
00:32:17.300 --> 00:32:19.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I will handle the Jem'Hadar.</i>

617
00:32:20.039 --> 00:32:22.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Who says there's never a Klingon around
when you need one?

618
00:32:22.998 --> 00:32:24.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckling )

619
00:32:28.196 --> 00:32:29.756  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shields at 35%.

620
00:32:31.171 --> 00:32:32.768  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're preparing for another attack.

621
00:32:33.555 --> 00:32:35.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Worf, make every shot count.

622
00:32:35.994 --> 00:32:37.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Attack wings and batteries,

623
00:32:38.093 --> 00:32:42.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
concentrate your firepower on Section 17
of the Outer Docking Ring.

624
00:32:42.892 --> 00:32:45.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have to penetrate their shields.

625
00:33:06.525 --> 00:33:08.524  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've lost main power to the shields.

626
00:33:08.765 --> 00:33:11.607  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Switching to auxiliary power,
but I do not know how long it will hold.

627
00:33:12.643 --> 00:33:13.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( yelling )

628
00:33:15.562 --> 00:33:17.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( beep )
-DAX:<i> </i>Defiant<i> to Captain Sisko.</i>

629
00:33:17.482 --> 00:33:18.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax, go ahead.

630
00:33:18.481 --> 00:33:19.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've set the last mine.

631
00:33:20.101 --> 00:33:21.922  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Activate the field and return
to the station.

632
00:33:22.040 --> 00:33:23.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Yes, sir. Dax out.</i>

633
00:33:32.277 --> 00:33:35.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Sir, the minefields--
-I have eyes, Damar.

634
00:33:35.356 --> 00:33:37.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This isn't turning out
quite the way I had planned.

635
00:33:37.755 --> 00:33:39.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's a minor setback, Weyoun.

636
00:33:40.654 --> 00:33:41.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Once we take the station,

637
00:33:41.815 --> 00:33:44.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we'll be able to dismantle the minefield
without interference.

638
00:33:45.224 --> 00:33:46.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Let's both hope your
confidence is justified.

639
00:33:49.049 --> 00:33:53.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Damar, signal the reserves
to prepare for a final assault.

640
00:33:55.446 --> 00:33:57.086  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Dominion fleet is regrouping.

641
00:33:57.165 --> 00:33:58.366  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( console beeping )

642
00:33:58.445 --> 00:34:01.684  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And I'm detecting another wave
of enemy ships entering Bajoran space.

643
00:34:02.448 --> 00:34:03.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are your orders, Captain?

644
00:34:04.408 --> 00:34:06.048  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've done all we can here.

645
00:34:06.587 --> 00:34:08.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Notify all remaining Starfleet personnel.

646
00:34:09.918 --> 00:34:11.747  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're evacuating the station.

647
00:34:21.875 --> 00:34:23.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
MAN: Report to the staging area.

648
00:34:26.673 --> 00:34:27.832  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
DAX: Worf!

649
00:34:27.913 --> 00:34:29.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia.

650
00:34:29.352 --> 00:34:31.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You should be on the <i>Defiant.</i>

651
00:34:31.907 --> 00:34:33.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I heard you're not coming with us,

652
00:34:33.087 --> 00:34:34.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that you've been assigned
to Martok's ship.

653
00:34:34.654 --> 00:34:36.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It may be some time
before we see each other again.

654
00:34:36.479 --> 00:34:38.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worf, we may never see each other again.

655
00:34:38.697 --> 00:34:41.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is war.
We must put aside our personal feelings

656
00:34:41.579 --> 00:34:42.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and focus on the task at hand.

657
00:34:43.268 --> 00:34:45.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've been through my share of wars.
I know what I have to do.

658
00:34:46.175 --> 00:34:47.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But before you leave,

659
00:34:48.735 --> 00:34:51.015  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want you to know
that the answer is "yes."

660
00:34:51.014 --> 00:34:53.013  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes... Yes to what?

661
00:34:53.013 --> 00:34:54.233  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, I will marry you.

662
00:34:55.412 --> 00:34:57.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's what you've wanted
from the beginning, isn't it?

663
00:34:58.532 --> 00:35:00.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

664
00:35:00.662 --> 00:35:01.442  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, it is.

665
00:35:01.451 --> 00:35:03.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then when all of this is over,
we'll get married.

666
00:35:05.370 --> 00:35:07.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And if that doesn't
give you a reason to survive,

667
00:35:08.976 --> 00:35:09.896  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know what will.

668
00:35:23.884 --> 00:35:28.007  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When I first took command of this post,
all I wanted was to be somewhere else...

669
00:35:28.922 --> 00:35:30.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
anywhere but here.

670
00:35:30.942 --> 00:35:32.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But now, five years later,

671
00:35:32.782 --> 00:35:36.024  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
this has become my home,
and you have become my family.

672
00:35:36.620 --> 00:35:38.081  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And leaving this station... leaving you...

673
00:35:38.719 --> 00:35:41.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is one of the hardest things
I've ever had to do.

674
00:35:42.179 --> 00:35:44.701  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>But this war isn't over yet.</i>

675
00:35:45.317 --> 00:35:48.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I want you to know that while we were </i>
<i>keeping the Dominion occupied,</i>

676
00:35:48.876 --> 00:35:52.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>a Starfleet-Klingon task force</i>
<i>crossed the border into Cardassia</i>

677
00:35:52.995 --> 00:35:57.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and destroyed the Dominion
shipyards on Torros III.

678
00:35:56.194 --> 00:35:57.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your sacrifices...

679
00:35:57.793 --> 00:36:00.913  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
our sacrifices made that victory possible.

680
00:36:02.472 --> 00:36:06.355  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But no victory can make
this moment any easier for me.

681
00:36:08.110 --> 00:36:11.252  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I promise, I will not rest

682
00:36:11.890 --> 00:36:13.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
until I stand with you again...

683
00:36:15.049 --> 00:36:17.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
here...

684
00:36:17.528 --> 00:36:18.929  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in this place where I belong.

685
00:36:24.286 --> 00:36:26.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sisko to <i>Defiant.</i>

686
00:36:26.285 --> 00:36:27.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
O'BRIEN: <i>Standing by, sir.</i>

687
00:36:29.457 --> 00:36:31.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-One to beam aboard.
<i>-Aye, Captain.</i>

688
00:36:38.861 --> 00:36:40.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Are we ready?
-As soon as you give the word, sir.

689
00:36:41.980 --> 00:36:44.039  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mr. Garak?

690
00:36:44.039 --> 00:36:44.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd like to come along, if you don't mind.

691
00:36:44.921 --> 00:36:46.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You never know when you
might need a good tailor.

692
00:36:47.159 --> 00:36:49.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And the simple fact is,
I have nowhere else to go.

693
00:36:50.677 --> 00:36:51.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Welcome aboard.

694
00:36:51.917 --> 00:36:53.545  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( beeping )
<i>-Dax to Sisko.</i>

695
00:36:53.545 --> 00:36:55.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The Dominion fleet</i>
<i>is coming around for another attack.</i>

696
00:36:56.196 --> 00:36:58.277  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Release docking clamps.
Prepare for departure.

697
00:37:17.110 --> 00:37:18.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( console beeping )

698
00:37:18.949 --> 00:37:20.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The <i>Defiant's </i>away.

699
00:37:21.528 --> 00:37:22.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Contact the Dominion fleet.

700
00:37:23.048 --> 00:37:23.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell them...

701
00:37:24.568 --> 00:37:27.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the Bajoran government
welcomes them to <i>Deep Space 9.</i>

702
00:37:28.807 --> 00:37:31.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( console beeps )
-Message acknowledged.

703
00:37:31.205 --> 00:37:32.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good.

704
00:37:32.865 --> 00:37:35.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's the last message this station
will be sending out for a while.

705
00:37:35.825 --> 00:37:36.944  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Computer...

706
00:37:36.944 --> 00:37:38.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
initiate program Sisko-1-9-7.

707
00:37:39.783 --> 00:37:41.343  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
COMPUTER: <i>Program initiated.</i>

708
00:37:57.857 --> 00:38:00.777  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Dukat wanted the station back.
He can have it.

709
00:38:02.256 --> 00:38:04.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't want to see a drop of root beer
left in this place.

710
00:38:05.455 --> 00:38:06.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Break out the kanar.

711
00:38:07.335 --> 00:38:09.535  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And find me some yamok sauce.

712
00:38:10.653 --> 00:38:11.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rom...

713
00:38:11.634 --> 00:38:14.216  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
assistant manager
for policy and clientele.

714
00:38:14.713 --> 00:38:15.794  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Reporting for work, Brother.

715
00:38:16.192 --> 00:38:18.591  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What, did you think you could
just walk back in here

716
00:38:18.591 --> 00:38:19.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and get your old job back?

717
00:38:19.431 --> 00:38:21.573  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Actually, I'm a spy...
working for Starfleet.

718
00:38:21.650 --> 00:38:23.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But don't tell anyone.

719
00:38:23.251 --> 00:38:25.802  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( quietly ) The Federation's
more desperate than I thought.

720
00:38:27.782 --> 00:38:29.889  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( aloud ) I knew one day
you'd come crawling back to me.

721
00:38:29.969 --> 00:38:32.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Now, get to work.
-Yes, Brother!

722
00:38:41.646 --> 00:38:42.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jake?

723
00:38:43.843 --> 00:38:45.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aren't you supposed to be on the <i>Defiant?</i>

724
00:38:45.863 --> 00:38:46.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I changed my mind.

725
00:38:48.022 --> 00:38:49.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's a war going on and...

726
00:38:49.773 --> 00:38:51.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm a reporter.

727
00:38:51.989 --> 00:38:52.889  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is where I belong.

728
00:38:58.579 --> 00:38:59.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But you're not safe here.

729
00:39:02.218 --> 00:39:05.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Dominion knows I'm the Emissary's son.

730
00:39:05.317 --> 00:39:06.097  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If they hurt me,

731
00:39:06.097 --> 00:39:09.469  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
they risk alienating their new friends,
the Bajorans.

732
00:39:11.436 --> 00:39:12.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I hope you're right.

733
00:39:14.354 --> 00:39:15.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So do I.

734
00:39:16.439 --> 00:39:17.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What the hell is Jake thinking?

735
00:39:18.433 --> 00:39:19.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do we go back for him?

736
00:39:19.814 --> 00:39:21.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can't risk the entire crew
for one man...

737
00:39:22.112 --> 00:39:23.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
even though he is my son.

738
00:39:23.193 --> 00:39:25.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And whether I like it or not, he is a man,

739
00:39:26.930 --> 00:39:28.691  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
capable of making his own choices.

740
00:39:32.569 --> 00:39:34.008  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maintain current course.

741
00:39:35.048 --> 00:39:36.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aye, Captain.

742
00:39:37.207 --> 00:39:40.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We should rendezvous with the Federation
task force in 48 hours.

743
00:39:41.127 --> 00:39:41.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And then what?

744
00:39:42.106 --> 00:39:45.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And then, we make the Dominion sorry
they ever set foot in the Alpha Quadrant.

745
00:39:45.785 --> 00:39:48.007  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Cadet, you took the words
right out of my mouth.

746
00:40:04.939 --> 00:40:07.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is a great victory for Cardassia.

747
00:40:07.781 --> 00:40:09.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And the Dominion.

748
00:40:09.458 --> 00:40:10.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Over 50 ships lost...

749
00:40:11.337 --> 00:40:13.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
our spacedocks on Torros III destroyed.

750
00:40:13.897 --> 00:40:15.878  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A victory perhaps, but a costly one.

751
00:40:16.036 --> 00:40:17.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll discuss the repercussions later.

752
00:40:18.756 --> 00:40:21.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right now, I'm going to enjoy this moment.

753
00:40:24.434 --> 00:40:27.536  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Gentlemen,
on behalf of the Bajoran government--

754
00:40:27.536 --> 00:40:29.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And the Promenade
Merchants' Association...

755
00:40:29.912 --> 00:40:32.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I officially welcome you to <i>Deep Space 9.</i>

756
00:40:33.091 --> 00:40:36.513  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You mean... <i>Terok Nor,</i> don't you?

757
00:40:40.249 --> 00:40:43.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Founder, we are honored
by your decision to remain with us.

758
00:40:43.746 --> 00:40:45.549  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not here as a Founder.

759
00:40:46.289 --> 00:40:48.149  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm the station's Chief of Security.

760
00:40:49.666 --> 00:40:50.607  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whatever you say.

761
00:40:50.626 --> 00:40:54.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Nevertheless, having a God walk amongst us
is most gratifying.

762
00:40:55.025 --> 00:40:55.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I agree.

763
00:40:57.304 --> 00:40:59.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You... me...

764
00:41:00.963 --> 00:41:01.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
the Major...

765
00:41:02.182 --> 00:41:03.043  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
together again.

766
00:41:04.182 --> 00:41:05.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It should be most interesting.

767
00:41:07.241 --> 00:41:10.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, if you'll excuse me,
I'll be in my office.

768
00:41:20.317 --> 00:41:22.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( static and hissing )

769
00:41:25.236 --> 00:41:28.675  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It would appear
Captain Sisko was most efficient

770
00:41:28.754 --> 00:41:30.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in disabling the station.

771
00:41:30.554 --> 00:41:31.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It can be repaired.

772
00:41:32.453 --> 00:41:33.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And it will be.

773
00:41:33.413 --> 00:41:36.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But your first priority
is to dismantle that minefield.

774
00:41:36.712 --> 00:41:39.254  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Until we can bring in
reinforcements from the Gamma Quadrant,

775
00:41:39.254 --> 00:41:40.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
our position here is vulnerable.

776
00:41:40.671 --> 00:41:42.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll deal with the minefields.

777
00:41:51.000 --> 00:41:54.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I assume Captain Sisko removed
or destroyed everything of value.

778
00:41:56.446 --> 00:41:57.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not everything.

779
00:42:03.156 --> 00:42:03.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is that?

780
00:42:05.043 --> 00:42:08.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A message... from Sisko.

781
00:42:08.539 --> 00:42:09.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't understand.

782
00:42:10.178 --> 00:42:11.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( chuckles )

783
00:42:11.617 --> 00:42:12.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's letting me know...

784
00:42:15.240 --> 00:42:16.021  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He'll be back.

